treads_scraper.users

users.queryuser(arg, dtsg: str, session_id: str) → Json
users.queryuser(arg: int, dtsg: str, session_id: str) → Json
users.queryuser(arg: str, dtsg: str, session_id: str) → Json

Returns a user profile by its user internal id (number) or it’s username (string) is matched.

Parameters:

  • arg (str) – unique user internal id.

  • arg – unique username of the user.

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session.

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session.

users.get_posts(username, dtsg, session_id)

Returns the most recent posts of a user by its internal user id.

Parameters:

  • username (str) – unique username of the user.

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session.

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session.

Returns:

Most recent posts of the user inside the list “edges”

Return type:

Json

users.get_replys(username, dtsg, session_id)

Returns the most recent replys of a user to other user’s posts and the posts it was originally replying. Similar to get_posts but por posts replying other users content.

Parameters:

  • username (str) – unique username of the user

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session

Returns:

List of “Edges” objects containing in each node at least 2 “thread items” being the first a post by other user and the seconf the reply from the specified user

Return type:

List[Edge]

users.scrap_all_posts(username: str, dtsg: str, session_id: str, limit: int = None, delay: int = 5)

Returns all posts or the most recent ones up to a specified limit of certain user using its internal user_id to perform the recursive queries. Each query is performed with certain delay to avoid banning the account for bot activity.

Parameters:

  • username (str) – unique username of the user

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session

  • limit (int) – Limit of posts to query. From most recent to older. None by default

  • delay (int) – Delay in seconds between each recursive query to avoid accounts suspensions for bot activity. 5 by default

Returns:

All posts of the user contained in the “edges” list.

Return type:

Json

users.scrap_all_replys(username: str, dtsg: str, session_id: str, limit: int = None, delay: int = 5)

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session

  • limit (int) – Limit of posts to query. From most recent to older. None by default

  • delay (int) – Delay in seconds between each recursive query to avoid accounts suspensions for bot activity. 5 by default

Returns:

Return type:

users.get_followers(username: int, dtsg: str, session_id: str)

Collects the latest users who followed an account likers of a post

Parameters:

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session.

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session.

  • limit (int) – Limit size of threads to crawl.

  • delay (int) – Delay among requests to avoid the account of getting suspended by bot activity.

Returns:

Return type:

Gets a thread with all its posts and crawls recursively all the replies up to the stablished limit.

Parameters:

  • postID (int) – Unique numerical identifier of a post.

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session.

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session.

  • limit (int) – Limit size of threads to crawl.

  • delay (int) – Delay among requests to avoid the account of getting suspended by bot activity.

Returns:

List of objects containing all information about a thread, its different posts and all the requested replies

Return type:

List (Edge)

threads_scraper.search

search.search_users(query: str, dtsg: str, session_id: str)

Searches user by the specified query.

Parameters:

  • query (str) – text to look users for. Potentially usernames or complete names.

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session

Returns:

List of most relevant results matching the query

Return type:

List[User]

search.search_posts(query: str, dtsg: str, session_id: str, limit: int = 10, delay: int = 5)

Performs a search of posts matching the query or posted by users whose username matches the query

Parameters:

  • query (str) – Search query.

  • dtsg (str) – Value generated by Facebook to validated the session

  • session_id (str) – Cookie identifier for the user session

  • limit (int, optional) – Maximum amount of posts to search for. Defaults to 10.

  • delay (int, optional) – Delay between requests in seconds. Defaults to 5.

Returns:

List of nodes containing the most relevant threads results matching the query.

Return type:

List[PostNode]
